<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>
A square has side length <m>{24}</m> cm. Find the area of the square.
</p>

<p>
Area = <fillin characters="8" name="ans1"/> <m>\text {cm}^2</m>  
</p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
The area of a square is found using the formula:
</p>

<p>
<me>
A = s^2
</me>
</p>

<p>
Here, the side length is:
</p>

<p>
<me>
s = {24}\text{ cm}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Substitute the value of the side into the formula.
</p>

<p>
<me>
A = {24}^2
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Multiply the side by itself.
</p>

<p>
<me>
A = {24} \times {24}
</me>
</p>

<p>
<me>
A = {576}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the area of the square is:
</p>

<p>
<me>
Area = {{576}\text{ cm}^2}
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>576</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>